Witnesses said the police dealt with around 2,000 demonstrators who had gathered outside the Colombo town hall Thursday afternoon , shouting anti-government slogans .
The protest against the government 's emergency regulations was organized by the leftist People 's Liberation Front , New Equal Society Party and the Muslim United Liberation Front with some trade unions .
Political rallies are banned under the emergency regulations introduced earlier this month .
The government has invoked the emergency regulations and placed the country on a war footing to fight Tamil Tiger rebels who are engaged in a ferocious assault in a bid to retake their former stronghold of Jaffna .
